 1589     {
 1590       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[76];
 1591       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);
 1592       if (ssGetErrorStatus(rts) != (NULL))
 1593         return;
 1594     }

 1621     {
 1622       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[80];

 1629     {
 1630       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[81];
 1631       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);

 1633         return;
 1634     }
 1635   
 1636     /* Level2 S-Function Block: '<S3>/Error_Indication' (LCInport) */
 1637     {
 1638       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[82];
 1639       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);
 1640       if (ssGetErrorStatus(rts) != (NULL))
 1641         return;
 1642     }
 1643   
 1644     /* Update absolute time for base rate */
 1645     /* The "clockTick0" counts the number of times the code of this task has
 1646      * been executed. The absolute time is the multiplication of "clockTick0"
 1647      * and "Timing.stepSize0". Size of "clockTick0" ensures timer will not
 1648      * overflow during the application lifespan selected.
 1649      * Timer of this task consists of two 32 bit unsigned integers.
 1650      * The two integers represent the low bits Timing.clockTick0 and the high bits
 1651      * Timing.clockTickH0. When the low bit overflows to 0, the high bits increment.
 1652      */
 1653     if (!(++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick0)) {
 1654       ++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH0;
 1655     }
 1656   
 1657     Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.t[0] = Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick0 *
 1658       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize0 +
 1659       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH0 *
 1660       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize0 * 4294967296.0;
 1661   
 1662     {
 1663       /* Update absolute timer for sample time: [0.01s, 0.0s] */
 1664       /* The "clockTick1" counts the number of times the code of this task has
 1665        * been executed. The absolute time is the multiplication of "clockTick1"
 1666        * and "Timing.stepSize1". Size of "clockTick1" ensures timer will not
 1667        * overflow during the application lifespan selected.
 1668        * Timer of this task consists of two 32 bit unsigned integers.
 1669        * The two integers represent the low bits Timing.clockTick1 and the high bits
 1670        * Timing.clockTickH1. When the low bit overflows to 0, the high bits increment.
 1671        */
 1672       if (!(++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick1)) {
 1673         ++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH1;
 1674       }
 1675   
 1676       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.t[1] = Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick1 *
 1677         Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize1 +
 1678         Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH1 *
 1679         Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize1 * 4294967296.0;
 1680     }
 1681   
 1682     /* tid is required for a uniform function interface.
 1683      * Argument tid is not used in the function. */
 1684     UNUSED_PARAMETER(tid);
 1685   }
